From: OpenAI Codex <codex@openai.com>
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: freescale: dpaa: compile and execute exact outbound egress recipe

Compile the supported Ethernet rewrite, redirect, NAT, VLAN push, and
PPPoE push flowtable actions into an explicit egress recipe owned by
each compiled DPAA flow entry, then teach the fresh-skb executor to
consume that recipe for one exact shaped outbound path.

This target-local patch is carried for OpenWrt Layerscape armv8_64b
(aarch64 little-endian). The offset-4 Ethernet pedit mapping below was
validated with passive on-wire capture on that target and should not be
read as proof for big-endian DPAA targets.

Keep the plain routed path unchanged. Continue rejecting broader shaped
recipes so shared-lower bridge handling, wider topology support, and
true FMAN-resident forwarding remain deferred.

---
